CHALLENGE 1
Task: Create a local repo with team.py containing two functions — greet() and farewell(). 
Push to GitHub. 
Create a branch feature-update and modify both functions differently on main and feature-update simultaneously. Merge, resolve both conflicts, and push clean final code to GitHub.

Done when: GitHub shows both branches, no conflict markers in team.py, and git log --oneline shows at 
least 5 commits (important). 

CHALLENGE 2

Task: Create a file notes.txt locally and push it to GitHub. 
Then make a change to the same file directly on GitHub (use GitHub's edit button), 
pull it back to your local machine and verify the change reflects locally.

Done when: Your local notes.txt matches what you edited on GitHub and git log --oneline shows 
commits from both sides.
